lithology: The sample was collected from a sandy coquina bed approximately 1 meter thick. This coquina occurs in a section of very thick bedded, medium to coarse grained, pebbly, blue-gray, calcareous, ashy carbonaceous, locally pyritic sandstone, interbedded with reddish-brown and grey bentonitic and gypsferous claystone. Lignite beds up to 5 cms. thick occur throughout the section.  Overlain unconformably by Quaternary pumaceous ash beds (avalanche deposits ). Underlain by Sepur formation (after Sapper, 1901.)
